Note:
AVL TREE - Strictly Balanced BST Tier 0 Primitive

This file implements an AVL tree, the original self-balancing BST.
AVL trees maintain a stricter balance than Red-Black trees: the height
difference between left and right subtrees of every node is at most 1.
This gives faster lookups (lower tree height) at the cost of slightly
more rotations on mutation.

Node structure (40 bytes):
  offset 0:  key (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  value (8 bytes)
  offset 16: left child pointer (8 bytes)
  offset 24: right child pointer (8 bytes)
  offset 32: height (8 bytes)

Tree structure (16 bytes):
  offset 0: root pointer
  offset 8: size

We use the "height stored at node" convention rather than balance-factor
because storing height makes height(nil) = 0 a natural sentinel, and
the rotation/rebalance code is more uniform than balance-factor variants.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let AVL_NODE_SIZE be 40
Let AVL_HEADER_SIZE be 16
Let AVL_KEY_OFFSET be 0
Let AVL_VALUE_OFFSET be 8
Let AVL_LEFT_OFFSET be 16
Let AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET be 24
Let AVL_HEIGHT_OFFSET be 32

Note: ============================================================================
Note: NODE HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Height of a (possibly null) subtree. Null = 0 so the recursive
identity height(x) = 1 + max(height(left), height(right)) holds.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 if node pointer is 0, else reads height field at offset 32.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_height" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_HEIGHT_OFFSET
End Process

@Reasoning
max(a, b) helper used inside the height update step. Inlined by the
backend.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Branch on a >= b.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_max" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is greater than or equal to b:
        Return a
    End If
    Return b
End Process

@Reasoning
Recompute height from children. Called after any structural change to
the children pointers.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
height = 1 + max(left.height, right.height).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_update_height" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
    Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
    Let lh be proc avl_height with left
    Let rh be proc avl_height with right
    Let new_h be 1 plus (proc avl_max with lh, rh)
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_HEIGHT_OFFSET, new_h
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Balance factor = left.height - right.height. -1, 0, +1 means balanced.
Values outside that range indicate which subtree is too tall and
trigger rotations.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 if node is null. Otherwise lh - rh.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_balance_factor" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
    Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
    Let lh be proc avl_height with left
    Let rh be proc avl_height with right
    Return lh minus rh
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a new leaf node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
40-byte alloc; key/value set; left/right = 0; height = 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_node_create" takes key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with AVL_NODE_SIZE
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_KEY_OFFSET, key
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_VALUE_OFFSET, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_HEIGHT_OFFSET, 1
    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ROTATIONS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Right rotation on y: y's left child x rises to take y's position, y
becomes x's right child, x's old right subtree becomes y's new left
subtree. Updates heights of both rotated nodes.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
x = y.left
T2 = x.right
x.right = y
y.left = T2
avl_update_height(y); avl_update_height(x)
return x as the new subtree root.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must have a non-null y.left.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_rotate_right" takes y as Integer returns Integer:
    Let x be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with y, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
    Let t2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with x, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with x, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, y
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, t2
    proc avl_update_height with y
    proc avl_update_height with x
    Return x
End Process

@Reasoning
Left rotation mirror of right.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Mirror of avl_rotate_right.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must have a non-null x.right.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_rotate_left" takes x as Integer returns Integer:
    Let y be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with x, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
    Let t2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with y, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, x
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with x, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, t2
    proc avl_update_height with x
    proc avl_update_height with y
    Return y
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: REBALANCE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
After an insert or delete updates the height chain, rebalance the
chain by inspecting the balance factor at each ancestor and rotating
when |bf| > 1.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Pure-function returns the new subtree root after rebalancing.
- Update height.
- Compute balance bf.
- If bf > 1 (left-heavy):
    - If left's balance >= 0: single right rotation.
    - Else: left-rotate left child first, then right-rotate (LR case).
- If bf < -1 (right-heavy):
    - If right's balance <= 0: single left rotation.
    - Else: right-rotate right child first, then left-rotate (RL case).
- Otherwise return node unchanged.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_rebalance" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc avl_update_height with node
    Let bf be proc avl_balance_factor with node
    If bf is greater than 1:
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
        Let left_bf be proc avl_balance_factor with left
        If left_bf is less than 0:
            Let new_left be proc avl_rotate_left with left
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, new_left
        End If
        Return proc avl_rotate_right with node
    End If
    If bf is less than 0 minus 1:
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
        Let right_bf be proc avl_balance_factor with right
        If right_bf is greater than 0:
            Let new_right be proc avl_rotate_right with right
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, new_right
        End If
        Return proc avl_rotate_left with node
    End If
    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TREE CONSTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Create an empty AVL tree.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
16-byte header; root = 0, size = 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_tree_create" returns Integer:
    Let tree be proc allocate from Layout with AVL_HEADER_SIZE
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, 0
    Return tree
End Process

@Reasoning
Free every node. Iterative postorder to bound stack depth.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Same stack-buffer technique as RB tree destroy. Maintain a dynamic
work buffer of node pointers, pop in postorder by pushing each child
back onto the stack.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(h).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_tree_destroy" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If root is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with tree
        Return 1
    End If
    Let cap be 64
    Let buf_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
    Let buf be proc allocate from Layout with buf_bytes
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sp be 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, 0, root
    Set sp to 1
    While sp is greater than 0:
        Set sp to sp minus 1
        Let off be sp multiplied by 8
        Let node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf, off
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
        Let need be sp plus 2
        If need is greater than cap:
            Let new_cap be cap multiplied by 2
            Let new_bytes be new_cap multiplied by 8
            Let new_buf be proc allocate from Layout with new_bytes
            If new_buf is equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                Return 0
            End If
            Let copy_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
            proc memory_copy from Memory with new_buf, buf, copy_bytes
            proc deallocate from Layout with buf
            Set buf to new_buf
            Set cap to new_cap
        End If
        If left is not equal to 0:
            Let l_off be sp multiplied by 8
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, l_off, left
            Set sp to sp plus 1
        End If
        If right is not equal to 0:
            Let r_off be sp multiplied by 8
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, r_off, right
            Set sp to sp plus 1
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with node
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with buf
    proc deallocate from Layout with tree
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Element count accessor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read size field.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_tree_size" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: INSERT (iterative with parent-chain rebalance)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Insert key/value. Walk down to find the insertion point, allocate the
leaf, then walk back up rebalancing. Because we do not store parent
pointers, we use a path stack to remember the ancestor chain.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) If tree empty, create root, size = 1.
2) Allocate a path-buffer of pointer-to-link slots: each slot stores
   a parent pointer plus a marker for left/right. Walk down recording
   each link, allocate the new node at the leaf.
3) Walk the path in reverse: at each ancestor, set its left/right
   child pointer to avl_rebalance(child_subtree). The avl_rebalance
   may return a different node as the new subtree root, in which case
   we relink the grandparent to that new root.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n). Space: O(log n) path buffer.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_tree_insert" takes tree as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If root is equal to 0:
        Let new_node be proc avl_node_create with key, value
        If new_node is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, new_node
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, 1
        Return 1
    End If
    Let max_path be 96
    Let path_bytes be max_path multiplied by 8
    Let path_nodes be proc allocate from Layout with path_bytes
    If path_nodes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let path_dirs be proc allocate from Layout with path_bytes
    If path_dirs is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
        Return 0
    End If
    Let depth be 0
    Let cur be root
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let cur_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_KEY_OFFSET
        Let off be depth multiplied by 8
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with path_nodes, off, cur
        If key is less than or equal to cur_key:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, off, 0
            Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
            If left is equal to 0:
                Let new_node be proc avl_node_create with key, value
                If new_node is equal to 0:
                    proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
                    proc deallocate from Layout with path_dirs
                    Return 0
                End If
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, new_node
                Set depth to depth plus 1
                Note: walk back up
                Let new_root be root
                While depth is greater than 0:
                    Set depth to depth minus 1
                    Let p_off be depth multiplied by 8
                    Let p_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_nodes, p_off
                    Let p_dir be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, p_off
                    Let target_child be 0
                    If p_dir is equal to 0:
                        Set target_child to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p_node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
                    Otherwise:
                        Set target_child to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p_node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
                    End If
                    Let rebalanced be proc avl_rebalance with target_child
                    If p_dir is equal to 0:
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p_node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, rebalanced
                    Otherwise:
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p_node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, rebalanced
                    End If
                    Let new_p be proc avl_rebalance with p_node
                    Set new_root to new_p
                    If depth is greater than 0:
                        Let pp_off be (depth minus 1) multiplied by 8
                        Let pp_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_nodes, pp_off
                        Let pp_dir be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, pp_off
                        If pp_dir is equal to 0:
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pp_node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, new_p
                        Otherwise:
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pp_node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, new_p
                        End If
                    End If
                End While
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, new_root
                Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, size plus 1
                proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
                proc deallocate from Layout with path_dirs
                Return 1
            End If
            Set cur to left
        Otherwise:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, off, 1
            Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
            If right is equal to 0:
                Let new_node be proc avl_node_create with key, value
                If new_node is equal to 0:
                    proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
                    proc deallocate from Layout with path_dirs
                    Return 0
                End If
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, new_node
                Set depth to depth plus 1
                Let new_root be root
                While depth is greater than 0:
                    Set depth to depth minus 1
                    Let p_off be depth multiplied by 8
                    Let p_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_nodes, p_off
                    Let p_dir be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, p_off
                    Let target_child be 0
                    If p_dir is equal to 0:
                        Set target_child to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p_node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
                    Otherwise:
                        Set target_child to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p_node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
                    End If
                    Let rebalanced be proc avl_rebalance with target_child
                    If p_dir is equal to 0:
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p_node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, rebalanced
                    Otherwise:
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p_node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, rebalanced
                    End If
                    Let new_p be proc avl_rebalance with p_node
                    Set new_root to new_p
                    If depth is greater than 0:
                        Let pp_off be (depth minus 1) multiplied by 8
                        Let pp_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_nodes, pp_off
                        Let pp_dir be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, pp_off
                        If pp_dir is equal to 0:
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pp_node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, new_p
                        Otherwise:
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pp_node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, new_p
                        End If
                    End If
                End While
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, new_root
                Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, size plus 1
                proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
                proc deallocate from Layout with path_dirs
                Return 1
            End If
            Set cur to right
        End If
        Set depth to depth plus 1
        If depth is greater than or equal to max_path:
            Note: Pathological height - this should never happen for a
            Note: correctly maintained AVL tree where depth is bounded
            Note: by log_phi(n+2). Abort to avoid path buffer overrun.
            proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
            proc deallocate from Layout with path_dirs
            Return 0
        End If
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
    proc deallocate from Layout with path_dirs
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SEARCH / MIN / MAX
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Search for key, return value, or 0 if absent.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Standard BST descent.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_tree_search" takes tree as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let ck be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_KEY_OFFSET
        If key is equal to ck:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_VALUE_OFFSET
        End If
        If key is less than ck:
            Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
        Otherwise:
            Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
        End If
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Contains predicate. Distinct from search so caller can differentiate
present-with-value-zero from absent.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
BST descent; return 1 on match, 0 on null.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_tree_contains" takes tree as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let ck be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_KEY_OFFSET
        If key is equal to ck:
            Return 1
        End If
        If key is less than ck:
            Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
        Otherwise:
            Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
        End If
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Min/max key lookups walk left or right from root.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk left children to min, right children to max.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_tree_min" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If cur is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
        If left is equal to 0:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_KEY_OFFSET
        End If
        Set cur to left
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Walk right children for the maximum key.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Mirror of min.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_tree_max" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If cur is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
        If right is equal to 0:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_KEY_OFFSET
        End If
        Set cur to right
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DELETE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Locate the in-order successor: the leftmost node of the right subtree
of 'node'. Used by delete to find the replacement key/value when the
deleted node has two children.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk left from node.right until a node with no left child is found.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_min_node" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be node
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
        If left is equal to 0:
            Return cur
        End If
        Set cur to left
    End While
    Return cur
End Process

@Reasoning
Public delete. Removes the entry whose key is equal to the given key
and rebalances. Returns 1 if deletion occurred, 0 if the key was not
present or the tree handle is invalid.

The algorithm:
1. Walk down recording the ancestor path until the node holding key
   is found (or determine absence).
2. Remove the node:
   - If node has 0 or 1 child: splice the (possibly null) child into
     the parent's pointer slot, free the node.
   - If node has 2 children: locate the in-order successor inside the
     right subtree. Copy the successor's key/value into the deleted
     node's slot, then delete the successor (which by definition has
     no left child, so it has at most 1 child). The path entries we
     record while walking to the successor are appended to the same
     path stack, so the subsequent rebalance walk fixes the entire
     chain in one pass.
3. Walk the recorded path in reverse, rebalancing at each ancestor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Path stack records (node, direction) pairs the same way insert does.
direction = 0 means "the child we descended into is the left child";
direction = 1 means "right child". After the deletion we re-fetch the
parent's child pointer (which may have been re-spliced), call
avl_rebalance to compute a possibly different subtree root, then
re-attach to its grandparent. The new root is also updated in the
tree header.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n) for the descent and the rebalance walk. Space:
O(log n) for the path buffers.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure or when the key is absent.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "avl_tree_delete" takes tree as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let max_path be 96
    Let path_bytes be max_path multiplied by 8
    Let path_nodes be proc allocate from Layout with path_bytes
    If path_nodes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let path_dirs be proc allocate from Layout with path_bytes
    If path_dirs is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: Locate the target node and record the path to its parent.
    Let depth be 0
    Let cur be root
    Let target be 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let cur_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_KEY_OFFSET
        If key is equal to cur_key:
            Set target to cur
            Set cur to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let off be depth multiplied by 8
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with path_nodes, off, cur
            If key is less than cur_key:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, off, 0
                Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
            Otherwise:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, off, 1
                Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
            End If
            Set depth to depth plus 1
            If depth is greater than or equal to max_path:
                proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
                proc deallocate from Layout with path_dirs
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    If target is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
        proc deallocate from Layout with path_dirs
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: target found; determine deletion strategy.
    Let t_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with target, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
    Let t_right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with target, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
    Let node_to_free be 0
    If t_left is not equal to 0 and t_right is not equal to 0:
        Note: two-children case. Find in-order successor (min of right
        Note: subtree). Record path from target to successor; the
        Note: successor sits at the leaf of those entries.
        Let succ_off be depth multiplied by 8
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with path_nodes, succ_off, target
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, succ_off, 1
        Set depth to depth plus 1
        If depth is greater than or equal to max_path:
            proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
            proc deallocate from Layout with path_dirs
            Return 0
        End If
        Let succ_parent be target
        Let succ be t_right
        Let succ_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with succ, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
        While succ_left is not equal to 0:
            Let s_off be depth multiplied by 8
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with path_nodes, s_off, succ
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, s_off, 0
            Set depth to depth plus 1
            If depth is greater than or equal to max_path:
                proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
                proc deallocate from Layout with path_dirs
                Return 0
            End If
            Set succ_parent to succ
            Set succ to succ_left
            Set succ_left to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with succ, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
        End While
        Note: Copy successor key/value into target. Successor has no
        Note: left child; only right child (possibly null) needs to
        Note: be spliced into the parent's slot.
        Let succ_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with succ, AVL_KEY_OFFSET
        Let succ_val be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with succ, AVL_VALUE_OFFSET
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with target, AVL_KEY_OFFSET, succ_key
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with target, AVL_VALUE_OFFSET, succ_val
        Let succ_right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with succ, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
        If succ_parent is equal to target:
            Note: successor was target.right directly; splice succ_right
            Note: into target's right pointer.
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with target, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, succ_right
        Otherwise:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with succ_parent, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, succ_right
        End If
        Set node_to_free to succ
    Otherwise:
        Note: zero- or one-child case. Replacement is whichever child
        Note: is non-null, or 0 if both are null.
        Let replacement be 0
        If t_left is not equal to 0:
            Set replacement to t_left
        Otherwise:
            Set replacement to t_right
        End If
        If depth is equal to 0:
            Note: deleting root with no two-children case; the
            Note: replacement becomes the new root directly.
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, replacement
        Otherwise:
            Let parent_off be (depth minus 1) multiplied by 8
            Let parent be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_nodes, parent_off
            Let p_dir be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, parent_off
            If p_dir is equal to 0:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parent, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, replacement
            Otherwise:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parent, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, replacement
            End If
        End If
        Set node_to_free to target
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with node_to_free
    Note: Walk back up rebalancing. At each ancestor:
    Note: 1. Re-fetch the child pointer that was modified.
    Note: 2. Call avl_rebalance on that child (in case the child
    Note:    itself is the rebalance target -- rebalance updates
    Note:    height and rotates if needed).
    Note: 3. Re-attach the rebalanced subtree.
    Note: 4. Then call avl_rebalance on the ancestor itself, since
    Note:    the height change can propagate upward.
    Let new_root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    While depth is greater than 0:
        Set depth to depth minus 1
        Let p_off be depth multiplied by 8
        Let p_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_nodes, p_off
        Let p_dir be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, p_off
        Let target_child be 0
        If p_dir is equal to 0:
            Set target_child to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p_node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET
        Otherwise:
            Set target_child to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p_node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET
        End If
        Let rebalanced_child be proc avl_rebalance with target_child
        If p_dir is equal to 0:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p_node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, rebalanced_child
        Otherwise:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with p_node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, rebalanced_child
        End If
        Let new_p be proc avl_rebalance with p_node
        Set new_root to new_p
        If depth is greater than 0:
            Let pp_off be (depth minus 1) multiplied by 8
            Let pp_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_nodes, pp_off
            Let pp_dir be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with path_dirs, pp_off
            If pp_dir is equal to 0:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pp_node, AVL_LEFT_OFFSET, new_p
            Otherwise:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pp_node, AVL_RIGHT_OFFSET, new_p
            End If
        End If
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, new_root
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, size minus 1
    proc deallocate from Layout with path_nodes
    proc deallocate from Layout with path_dirs
    Return 1
End Process
